149
00:11:56,389 --> 00:12:01,351
I do hope you understand. Your friend, Rarity.

150
00:12:01,352 --> 00:12:04,852
I suppose this means you don't need me to bring down your bags?

151
00:12:04,853 --> 00:12:08,498
No.
But, I will need some help unpacking them.

152
00:12:12,004 --> 00:12:13,889
What do you think? Too much?

153
00:12:15,589 --> 00:12:17,195
You're right. Too little.

154
00:12:18,177 --> 00:12:20,392
Garden party, here I come!

155
00:12:21,162 --> 00:12:22,956
Surprise!

156
00:12:26,732 --> 00:12:29,736
Swoosh! And right before she hit the ground, shoom, she-

157
00:12:29,737 --> 00:12:31,037
Hi again!

158
00:12:31,038 --> 00:12:33,756
What are you- how did you- Why are you-

159
00:12:33,757 --> 00:12:37,584
Listen to her, she's so excited to see us she can hardly talk.

160
00:12:37,585 --> 00:12:40,628
What I mean to say is, what are you all doing here?

161
00:12:40,629 --> 00:12:43,441
When I got your letter saying you were stuck in Canterlot,

162
00:12:43,442 --> 00:12:47,154
I asked Pinkie Pie if it wouldn't be too much trouble to move my birthday party here,

163
00:12:47,155 --> 00:12:48,655
so you wouldn't have to miss it!

164
00:12:48,656 --> 00:12:50,640
Balloons are super easy to pack.

165
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:59,080
First you get me a suite at Canterlot castle and now this...

166
00:12:59,081 --> 00:13:01,515
I don't know what to say, Twilight.

167
00:13:01,516 --> 00:13:05,620
How about you start by saying what you're doing in that fancy getup?

168
00:13:05,621 --> 00:13:13,365
This? Well I always put on something a little fancy when Opal's feeling under the weather...

169
00:13:13,366 --> 00:13:14,366
Cheers her right up.

170
00:13:16,103 --> 00:13:19,512
Oh, poor Opal, where is the sick darling?

171
00:13:19,513 --> 00:13:22,474
Uh, she's... hold on a minute.

172
00:13:26,732 --> 00:13:28,711
I am so sorry about this.

173
00:13:36,244 --> 00:13:37,878
She's resting on the bed.

174
00:13:38,079 --> 00:13:41,967
Poor baby. She looks awful.

175
00:13:43,772 --> 00:13:46,140
Is... that my dress?

176
00:13:46,241 --> 00:13:47,241
Yes.

177
00:13:47,842 --> 00:13:50,274
It's so... simple.

178
00:13:50,275 --> 00:13:51,575
So practical...

179
00:13:51,976 --> 00:13:56,329
So me! It's the perfect dress for my birthday party!

180
00:13:56,330 --> 00:13:57,530
I love it!

181
00:13:59,103 --> 00:14:02,097
You don't know how glad I am to hear you say that.

182
00:14:05,839 --> 00:14:08,861
When I told the Princess that I was moving the party to Canterlot,

183
00:14:08,862 --> 00:14:12,453
she was kind enough to offer us the Canterlot castle ballroom!

184
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:15,794
Isn't it fancy pants?

185
00:14:15,795 --> 00:14:18,106
Fancy Pants?! Where?!

186
00:14:20,278 --> 00:14:25,117
I mean, where did you find the time to put up all these decorations?

187
00:14:27,516 --> 00:14:30,410
I never leave home without my party cannon.

188
00:14:35,109 --> 00:14:40,346
I thought about having my birthday outside, but they're having another party on the castle grounds today.

189
00:14:48,374 --> 00:14:50,502
Let's party!

190
00:15:16,938 --> 00:15:19,635
No reason I can't at least make an appearance...

191
00:15:30,064 --> 00:15:32,195
I'm here!

192
00:15:32,496 --> 00:15:35,115
Darling, I'm so glad you made it.

193
00:15:35,316 --> 00:15:38,527
Rarity! So happy to see you here.

194
00:15:38,528 --> 00:15:41,053
I wouldn't have missed this for the world.

195
00:15:42,059 --> 00:15:46,283
I say, what is that scent you're wearing? It smells like...

196
00:15:46,284 --> 00:15:48,500
...is that cake frosting?

197
00:15:49,619 --> 00:15:53,514
Yes, I always dab a little frosting behind my ears before I go out.

198
00:15:54,849 --> 00:15:57,957
After all, who doesn't like the smell of cake frosting?

199
00:15:58,772 --> 00:16:00,265
I know I do.

200
00:16:02,348 --> 00:16:05,546
Well, all this talk about cake has made me hungry.

201
00:16:05,547 --> 00:16:09,608
Think I'll go and see what's on the hors d'oeuvres table. If you'll excuse me.

202
00:16:49,754 --> 00:16:52,162
I think I left the bathwater running in my suite.

203
00:16:53,219 --> 00:16:55,206
I really should go check on Opal...

204
00:16:55,413 --> 00:16:57,524
Is that Princess Celestia?

205
00:16:57,525 --> 00:16:59,467
I need to use the little fillies room!

206
00:16:59,468 --> 00:17:01,271
Can I get anypony more punch?

207
00:17:01,272 --> 00:17:06,432
I... have to go to do the... thing with the... stuff in uh...

208
00:17:06,433 --> 00:17:08,537
What's with the croquet mallet?

209
00:17:08,538 --> 00:17:09,538
What croquet mallet?

210
00:17:09,539 --> 00:17:11,705
Duh, the one in your mouth!

211
00:17:14,097 --> 00:17:19,883
Oh, that croquet mallet.
I- well I, you know, the truth is... the truth is...

212
00:17:19,884 --> 00:17:22,625
Were you at that other party in the garden?

213
00:17:23,238 --> 00:17:25,652
I, I...

214
00:17:25,953 --> 00:17:28,750
Rarity, I'm surprised at you.

215
00:17:28,751 --> 00:17:30,477
Twilight let me explain! I-

216
00:17:30,478 --> 00:17:33,503
I hadn't realized you were such a savvy businesspony!

217
00:17:33,504 --> 00:17:35,289
You must understand! I-

218
00:17:35,590 --> 00:17:38,119
All of those ponies look so posh.

219
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:43,188
And with the Grand Galloping Gala coming up, I bet you could totally get some of them to buy your dresses.

220
00:17:43,189 --> 00:17:44,289
Very smart!

221
00:17:45,994 --> 00:17:53,702
Why yes, I didn't want you to think I was being rude, so that's exactly the reason I didn't tell you.

222
00:17:53,803 --> 00:17:55,688
One and only reason.

223
00:17:57,459 --> 00:18:01,226
Well you didn't have to do that. You should totally go over there and mingle!

224
00:18:02,027 --> 00:18:06,739
Twilight, you really are the best friend a pony could ever ask for.

225
00:18:06,740 --> 00:18:09,842
I don't know why I ever thought you wouldn't understand.

226
00:18:09,843 --> 00:18:11,191
Understand what?

227
00:18:11,192 --> 00:18:13,599
Nothing. See you girls later!

228
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:15,991
Hey, wait up!

229
00:18:15,992 --> 00:18:17,240
We're your friends!

230
00:18:17,241 --> 00:18:19,703
I'm sure they won't mind if we check out the party too!

231
00:18:19,704 --> 00:18:23,861
C'mon you guys! Let's show them how to party Ponyville style!

232
00:18:26,836 --> 00:18:28,845
Oh no!

233
00:18:54,078 --> 00:18:56,317
How come y'all aren't doing any gardening?

234
00:18:56,318 --> 00:18:58,590
This is a garden party, isn't it?

235
00:19:04,592 --> 00:19:07,513
