It's just so plain.

237
00:19:09,906 --> 00:19:10,906
Yeah.

238
00:19:12,096 --> 00:19:16,783
Excuse me, might I ask where you got your ensemble?

239
00:19:16,784 --> 00:19:18,891
Why yes, yes you may.

240
00:19:18,892 --> 00:19:23,082
A very, very close friend of mine from Ponyville made it for me.

241
00:19:26,170 --> 00:19:28,505
Ponyville? You don't say?

242
00:19:28,506 --> 00:19:30,547
I do say. Her name is-

243
00:19:30,548 --> 00:19:31,991
Fancy Pants! Come with me!

244
00:19:31,992 --> 00:19:35,175
I'd like to show you this... thing... that's over there.

245
00:19:35,176 --> 00:19:36,276
On the other side of the room.

246
00:19:36,277 --> 00:19:37,824
In a moment, my dear.

247
00:19:37,825 --> 00:19:43,510
This lovely filly from Ponyville was just about to tell me who made her charming dress.

248
00:19:43,511 --> 00:19:46,834
That dress? Oh come now, who cares, it's just a plain old-

249
00:19:46,835 --> 00:19:50,244
Oh don't be so modest, this dress you made is beautiful!

250
00:19:54,856 --> 00:19:56,912
We all think so!

251
00:19:57,713 --> 00:19:59,874
You know these ponies?

252
00:20:12,655 --> 00:20:15,204
Yes. Yes, I do know them.

253
00:20:15,205 --> 00:20:18,496
They may not be as sophisticated as some of you Canterlot ponies,

254
00:20:18,497 --> 00:20:20,308
but they are my best friends.

255
00:20:20,309 --> 00:20:24,380
And they are without a doubt the most important ponies I know.

256
00:20:25,358 --> 00:20:28,996
Important ponies? These ruffians?

257
00:20:28,997 --> 00:20:31,124
Don't make me laugh!

258
00:20:32,956 --> 00:20:36,356
I, for one, find them charmingly rustic.

259
00:20:37,673 --> 00:20:40,934
And I think the dress you made for your friend is lovely.

260
00:20:41,645 --> 00:20:45,211
I dare say every mare in Canterlot will be wanting one.

261
00:20:45,212 --> 00:20:48,114
I'd like to place my order right now.

262
00:20:48,115 --> 00:20:49,819
I think you should get two.

263
00:20:51,616 --> 00:20:56,277
Yes, now then, how about you introduce me to your friends?

264
00:20:56,278 --> 00:20:57,478
With pleasure!

265
00:20:59,558 --> 00:21:01,672
Dear Princess Celestia,

266
00:21:01,673 --> 00:21:05,797
I wanted to tell you about the important lesson I learned during my visit.

267
00:21:05,798 --> 00:21:08,312
Now that I would like to hear.

268
00:21:08,313 --> 00:21:11,209
I learned that no matter where you go in life,

269
00:21:11,210 --> 00:21:14,946
you should never forget that you are the product of your home and your friends.

270
00:21:14,947 --> 00:21:19,329
And that is something always to be proud of, no matter what.

271
00:21:19,930 --> 00:21:22,949
A very valuable lesson to have learned.

272
00:21:22,950 --> 00:21:24,150
It certainly is!

273
00:21:24,151 --> 00:21:28,067
But... might I ask that we hurry things up a bit?!

